Journal

How are you?

   



Mental well-being is vital at every stage of life.



It brings many benefits to your daily life.



It gives you an elevated sense of purpose,



an optimistic perspective for new experiences,



and produces a positive impact in your mood.



However, mental health services are not accessible to everyone.



In the UK, around 8 million people are not in contact with health services.



Around 1 billion people are living with a mental disorder.



Half of the world's population will experience a mental health condition.



Around 1 in 7 teenagers struggle with mental health.



Lower-income countries have less than one mental health professional per 100,000 citizens.



The global economy loses nearly 1 trillion US dollars every year due to anxiety and depression.



Mental well-being is our right, and it should be free.

Welcome to the future of mental well-being.

Sources:
World Health Organization (who.int)
The Guardian (theguardian.com)
Project Hope (projecthope.org)
UN News (news.un.org)
